<dl id="n12006g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12006g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12006g"> 6(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Dol, truce between armies / prophecy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il y en a enfin qui <mark>ont surgi miraculeusement du sol pour s&eacute;parer deux arm&eacute;es</mark> qui combattaient. De ce nombre est le beau monolithe du Champ-Dolent, pr&egrave;s <mark>Dol</mark>, qui a 9 m. 30 de hauteur, et que sans nul doute beaucoup d&apos;entre vous connaissent. Il a, de plus, cette particularit&eacute; assez rare d&apos;&ecirc;tre dou&eacute; <mark>du don de proph&eacute;tie</mark>. <br><font color="green">[Finally there are some that miraculously rose out of the ground in order to separate two armies engaged in combat. One of these is the beautiful monolith at Champ-Dolent, near Dol, which is 9.30 metres tall and is, without any doubt, known by many of you. It also has been granted something very rare, the gift of prophecy]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 20</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
